[{"id":"VR022163","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Which of the following is an example of how the consumer price index <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"open parenthesis, C P I, close parenthesis\"><math alttext=\"open parenthesis, C P I, close parenthesis\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mo>(</mo><mtext>C</mtext><mtext>P</mtext><mtext>I</mtext><mo>)</mo></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> exhibits bias in its estimates of changes in the cost of living?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR022163_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Energy prices have a higher impact on inflation than other input costs do.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">New products are always overrepresented in the <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"C P I\"><math alttext=\"C P I\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>C</mtext><mtext>PI</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"C P I\"><math alttext=\"C P I\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>C</mtext><mtext>PI</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> assigns greater weight to measures of welfare than it does to economic activity.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Product improvements are not always fully reflected in the calculation of the <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"C P I\"><math alttext=\"C P I\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>C</mtext><mtext>PI</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"C P I\"><math alttext=\"C P I\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>C</mtext><mtext>PI</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> adjusts for the substitution of less expensive goods by consumers.</p>"],"answer":3}]